dimensions

public java.util.List<DataDimensionMetadata> dimensions
The metadata associated with each of the dimensions of this DataTable. If the data table is found to be non-rectangular, then this will be null (because it would be meaningless)

Constructor Detail

DataTable

public DataTable(java.util.List<java.util.List<java.lang.String>> stringsTable)
Constructs a data table from the given table of Strings. If a string represents a valid number, it becomes a data entry with a double value and no string value.If a string does not represent a valid number, it becomes a data entry with the original string value, and a double value based on that string's ID within that dimension.

Parameters:
stringsTable - the table of Strings build the data table from

DataTable

public DataTable(java.util.List<java.util.List<java.lang.String>> stringsTable,
                 java.lang.String name)
Constructs a data table from the given table of Strings and name. If a string represents a valid number, it becomes a data entry with a double value and no string value.If a string does not represent a valid number, it becomes a data entry with the original string value, and a double value based on that string's ID within that dimension.

Parameters:
stringsTable - the table of Strings build the data table from
name - the name of this dataset, used for displaying

getSelectionsAsBits

public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getSelectionsAsBits()
Returns:
the current list of selections represented as bit sets encoded into Strings using base-64 encoding, or null if there are no selections.

setSelectionsAsBits

public void setSelectionsAsBits(java.util.List<java.lang.String> selectionsAsBits)
Sets the current list of selections to be a new list popupated with selections derived by decoding the specified base-64 encoded String into a bit set (in which the indices of the bit set's set bits (the '1' bits) correspond to the indices of the records to put in the selection). Then the drawing panels are updated.

Parameters:
selectionsAsBits - the list of Strings (base-64 encoded bit sets) to derive the new list of selections from.
